Subnets: Dividing your VPC into smaller networks(like rooms in your house)(public or private).
Route Tables: Control traffic flow between subnets and other networks.
Internet Gateway (IGW): Allows VPC  to connect to the internet. (like a door to outside world)
NAT Gateway: Allows private instances to access the internet without being directly exposed.
Security Groups: Virtual firewalls to control inbound and outbound traffic for resources.


